KABUL, Dec. 9 (Xinhua) -- The World Health Organization (WHO) has commenced construction of a new trauma center in a remote district in Afghanistan's southern province of Kandahar, the agency announced on Thursday. As part of efforts to expand trauma services across Afghanistan, WHO has commenced construction of a new trauma care unit (TCU) in Spin Boldak district, with support from European Union Commission Civil Protection and Humanitarian Aid, the agency said in a tweet. The TCU building construction will be completed in three months and half, the agency said. The WHO is supporting 130 TCUs across the war-hit Asian country. Enditem